detail_description: Nestled in the stunning coastal town of Ubatuba, the Ubatuba Aquarium is a delightful blend of indoor and outdoor experiences that showcases an impressive array of local marine life. detail_description: Nestled near the stunning Praia da Lagoinha, the Ruínas da Lagoinha (Fazenda Bom Retiro) offers a captivating glimpse into Ubatuba's rich history. Once a thriving coffee plantation in the 17th century, this site showcases remnants of stone and lime structures believed to have been built in 1828 by French engineer Stevenne. The area also features a glass factory established by Captain Romualdo, who sought to produce bottles for his aguardente exports.
